Reasoning: The paper discusses the process of information retrieval in the legal domain using natural language processing techniques and vector space representations. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep learning models also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the study involves the analysis of semantic word measures, which could potentially fall under the sub-category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
